Description:
    The install generator sets up RailsComponents in your Rails application by:
    - Creating a configuration initializer
    - Setting up Stimulus controller integration
    - Configuring importmap for engine controllers
    - Updating Tailwind configuration with engine paths
    - Copying DaisyUI plugin configuration

Example:
    bin/rails generate kumiki:install

    This will create:
        config/initializers/kumiki.rb
        app/assets/javascripts/daisyui.js
        app/javascript/application.js (if not exists)

    And update:
        config/importmap.rb
        config/tailwind.config.js (or other detected Tailwind config)
        app/javascript/application.js (if exists)

Options:
    --form-builder
        Enable RailsComponents form builder as the default for all forms.
        When enabled, all form_with calls automatically use RailsComponents::ApplicationFormBuilder

    --no-preview-system
        Disable the component preview system.
        By default, previews are enabled in development and test environments.

Examples:
    bin/rails generate kumiki:install --form-builder
    bin/rails generate kumiki:install --no-preview-system
    bin/rails generate kumiki:install --form-builder --no-preview-system
